                            <handNote><q>The inscription is in capitals... In line 1 VA are ligatured; the horizontal of the L slopes downwards, the first stroke of the N is slightly extended and the terminating I is horizontal. In line 2 VN are ligatured. In line 3 the outer strokes of the M are widely spaced and the inner strokes touch the line; MA are conjoined; R has a shortened diagonal and S in elongated.</q><bibl><ptr target ="EDW2007"/>Edwards 2007<citedRange unit="page">498</citedRange></bibl>.
